The paper focuses on the quality assurance, security, and interpretation of deep learning systems, which are all relevant to software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the vulnerabilities and defects of deep learning systems, which are related to cybersecurity, indicating that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the success of deep learning in various applications, such as intelligent machines and medical diagnostics, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the urgent demands for rigorous methodologies and engineering practice for quality enhancement, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
